	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well ok dude i see that u have not made a mage yet. Well yes u need the component Malachite. But then when u hit lvl 12 u need to use Lapiz for ur lvl 12 and 16 pets. Then once u hit lvl 20 and get ur new pets u use malachiet again and you use it for the rest of ur mages life. THis is a pointless thing to do. U only use Lapiz for 2 different pet lvls. The only thing is that Malachite cost 1 SILVER and Lapiz Cost 1 GOLD. Hard lesson to get by but i didnt make the game. And im not sure what u mean by strongest spell but i think u mean pet And well there are differences. Let me tell u the use for each pet.<br><br><br>FIRE- the most damaging pet and crates its own fire shield that always better then the current one u have. HP is absolutley horrible though. Dont use this pet unless u are in a group. Has a fire attack spell too.<br><br>EARTH- The most HP and has a root spell on him. It sucks though only lastign for 10 seconds. but her recast it about that often. Weakest Damage.<br>U can use this pet good for soloing.<br><br>WATER- personal favorite. Has great AC and only a little less then Earth. Trust me the AC makes up for the HP loss against fire. HAs a ice attack that is equal to the fire pet burn spell. My favorte for soloing since it can attack better then earth and has an atack spell.<br><br>AIR- One of the uncommonly used pets. This pet has a nice attack about the same as Water. The spell on this pet is a stunn spell that is great. The Agility on this pet is far greater then anythign else which equals great Defensive potentials and makes up for its okay HP. And this pet also cast an invisible spell on itself if hes not used so dont worry if he disappears. This would have to be my all around favorite pet unlike others who think its usless. <br><br>Well goodluck I hope this helps you out. <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
