	   <tr><td colspan=2>Ok, Im kinda new to EQ, and this is my first mage. Im L8 with all my spells. I did my first LARGE grouping today and have some questions on general rules of the classes. I was Using pets pretty well(I have practiced this SOLO for a while) and Nuking till Im out of mana, then stepping in only if someone is about to die.<br><br>The group had 1Cleric, 2 Necros, 1 Mage(me), A monk, and a few others that rotated in and out. I did what I was told by the group leader, I learned quick when someone pulled while we werent ready and didnt even tell anyone!!!!&nbsp;&nbsp;3 Orc's conning red wiped up all out!<br><br>I did the basics of reporting mana (20m, 40m, etc etc) to the leader, and made Sure to 'assist' the guy pulling even if two came out!<br><br>So what are the rules? Or is it just .. "do what the leader sais' ?  All in all I think I did well. Most of us hit 2 levels in about an hour.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
