	   <tr><td colspan=2>I found an incredible place to hunt at 26 (with another mage friend of the same level), and I'm still hunting there (solo)now at 30 (ummm...4 days later).&nbsp;&nbsp;29th level took me about 5 hours.<br><br>Try the golras in Timorous Deep.  Excellent exp. Small aggro range.  They hit hard, but are well worth it (usually hitting for around 60...I saw one double hit for 60).  They drop an avg of 2pp, and words that can be used on 29 spells as well.<br><br>Check out <a href="http://www.eqatlas.com," target=_new>http://www.eqatlas.com,</a> and look for Halara's island in Timorous Deep.  <br><br>The island is an iceberg, with only 2 spots where you can get out of the water, and onto the island.  Be VERY careful to not get too close to the edge, and pull a Golra on you.  I've seen 2 guild mates die by getting too close to a Golra while still in the water.<br><br>Golras are lvl26 to 29, hulking golras are 33 to 36, and Halara is past 40 (I don't suggest trying him, though, I saw a lvl52 monk die last night trying to take him - took me out as well because I was Damage Shielding the monk).<br><br>Nobody goes here.  It is a great place.  Shhh!  Don't tell anybody!<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
