<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98670461054353></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98670461054353><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=12&mid=98670461054353>RE: beginer quistion</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=12&mid=98670461054353#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Apr 8th 12:36 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Yes, all of your pets will require a component. Pets at level 4-8, and 20-60, will require malachite. Pets at levels 12-16 will require lapis lazuli.<br><br>The gem is consumed each time you create a new pet.<br><br>At lower levels, this makes your pet quite an expensive investment. Thankfully, you are still in a pretty good position to step in and take a few hits to save your pet from dying. At level 8, you get the ability to heal your pet.<br><br>At higher levels, your pet will be very inexpensive...buying two or three stacks of malachite will just be a normal part of your shopping trips in town.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
	   </form></table><ul>
<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98716888462389></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98716888462389><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=12&mid=98716888462389>RE: beginer quistion</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=12&mid=98716888462389#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=887><span id=Sage>Zuranthium</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>390 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Apr 13th 9:34 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.95]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>The components for the pets are very cheap, and can be bought at any gem shop. At levels 4-11 and levels 20-60 you will need malachite for your pet, which costs about 6 silver each. At levels 12-19 it changes to lapis lazuli for some odd reason, and they cost about 1 gold each.<br><br>If you are a gnome magician you can find your components in steamfont. After exiting the city of Aakanon, just follow the wall to the right until you get to a small group of shops. In the shop to the far right, there will be a man selling gems.<br><br>For all of the other races, there are gem shops in their towns, which are easy to find.<br><br>Former Addict of Everquest.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
