<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98633011956980></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98633011956980><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=12&mid=98633011956980>RE: Pets</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=12&mid=98633011956980#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=887><span id=Sage>Zuranthium</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>390 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Apr 3rd 4:35 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>At the lower levels don't even bother with the air pet unless you are using it just for fun. At the lower levels its high agility doesn't do crap since the pets don't have their dogde skills built up. Also at lower levels the air pet casts its stun spell less often, so it isn't ass efficient. However, at higher levels it becomes a good tank, and is great when fighting casters becuase of its stun spell, and is good to have in dungeons becuase of the invisibility that it casts on itself.<br><br>The fire pet DOES do the most damage if it is getting hit. The best feature of the fire pet is its damage shield. Right after you cast it, it will damage shield it self with a damage shield about 2x as good as the you one you can cast at your level. In addition to simply being better than your damage shield, the fire pet saves you mana. When using other pets you have to damage shield them before every fight. With the fire pet you don't need to waste your mana on damage shields. The fire pet also casts some good fire-based direct damage spells. The only problem with the pet is that it has absolutely horrible HP, so you need to kill your opponents quickly when using it.<br><br>The water pet is pretty much the overall decent pet. Good HP, good AC, good damage, is immune to poison, and regens HP very quickly. It is not the best in any category, but is very well rounded, and its additional abilities are nice to have in some situations( the poison immunity and fast HP-regen).<br><br>The earth pet is the pet you want when fighting big things. It will last longer in a fight than any other pet. It also casts a root spell which is good and bad. It is good when you don't want your enemy to run away, or when you don't want your enemy coming after you. It is sometimes bad becuase when you are fighting creatures that flee, then instead of fleeing, they will stay there and fight while rooted. Since they keep fighting they might kill your pet, or you will have to spend more mana to kill it. Overall at the lower levels the earth pet is the best for soloing IMO.<br><br>Former Everquest Addict.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
