	   <tr><td colspan=2>Have never had any problems soloing a mage.&nbsp;&nbsp;It does take practice however.  If the MOB is not real low on hit points and your pet dies chances are you die unless you have practiced conjuring another pet while in a fight.  You don't have the evac means that some other classes have.<br><br>Some say mages are good for newbies who want to be full casters.  Well they are at lower levels but can get frustrating at higher levels with the difficult and expensive research.  But I have played all of the full casters and find the mages to be the most challenging and fun to play.<br><br>Soloing is easier due to the fact that you have a built in tank for you that has casting capibilities.  You just have to practice and learn how to use this tank and which tank to use in certain situations.<br><br>Azamar<br>45 season mage of Tallon Zek.<br><br>&nbsp;<br>Azamar<br></td></tr>
