	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Mar 29th 9:20 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>My prefernce in all roleplaying games is to be an elf, so I'm biased. If you want to travel safely in cities, be a High Elf. If you like a challenge and being able to see places in the game most people don't, be a Dark Elf. Also, I have a Mage, Druid and Necro and can say that using the one handed (1H Blunt) staff as your melee weapon in the beginning will pay off later. Better damage in the long run (even with higher delay). Either buy a 1H Blunt staff or just arm one that a mob drops. On pets: you'll end up using water or earth all the time anyway, so I'll spare you the money wasting of buying air or fire pets until later levels when their specific talents become useful. Also, buy True North and keep Divination maxed because you'll need that when Invisibility becomes available.<br>Hope this helps a bit.<br>&nbsp;<br>Aaneldarie Tura'Seorsa<br>29th Season Magician&nbsp;&nbsp;Vazaelle</td></tr>
